# GitLab Issue Queue Bot Configuration
# Copy this file to .env or set these as environment variables

# Required Settings
GITLAB_TOKEN=your_gitlab_personal_access_token_here
PROJECT_ID=123456

# Optional Settings
GITLAB_URL=https://gitlab.com
LABEL=auto-generated
ASSIGNEES=username1,username2
POLL_INTERVAL=900

# Settings Explanation:
#
# GITLAB_TOKEN (Required)
#   - Personal Access Token or CI Job Token with 'api' scope
#   - Create at: GitLab > Settings > Access Tokens
#   - Scopes needed: api
#
# PROJECT_ID (Required)  
#   - Numeric project ID (visible in project overview)
#   - NOT the project name or URL path
#   - Example: 12345678
#
# GITLAB_URL (Optional)
#   - GitLab instance URL
#   - Default: https://gitlab.com
#   - For self-hosted: https://gitlab.your-company.com
#
# LABEL (Optional)
#   - Label applied to all bot-created issues
#   - Used to identify and track bot issues
#   - Default: auto-generated
#
# ASSIGNEES (Optional)
#   - Comma-separated list of GitLab usernames
#   - Users to automatically assign to new issues
#   - Example: alice,bob,charlie
#
# POLL_INTERVAL (Optional)
#   - Seconds between checks in continuous mode
#   - Default: 900 (15 minutes)
#   - Only used with --continuous flag
